info.headline: Flood Warning issued January 10 at 9:56AM EST by NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM EST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected. * WHERE...Portions of central Delaware, including the following county, Kent and northeast Maryland, including the following counties, Caroline, Queen Anne`s and Talbot. * WHEN...Until 500 PM EST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 955 AM EST, flooding was ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the warned area. Between 3 and 4 inches of rain have fallen. - For Choptank at Greensboro: At 9:15am the stage was 8.79 feet. Flood Stage is 9 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Turn around...don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
